<subSubSection pageId="69" pageNumber="70" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="69.[151,1437,796,1974]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,903,930]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Abdalla &amp; Mansell &amp; Sole" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Tjeder" baseAuthorityYear="1967" box="[330,555,904,930]" class="Insecta" family="Nemopteridae" genus="Afroptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="segregata">
<emphasis box="[330,555,904,930]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Afroptera segregata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[708,821,904,930]" class="Insecta" family="Nemopteridae" genus="Nemopterella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="munroi">
<emphasis box="[708,821,904,930]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">A. munroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, being of similar size, shape of the forewings and abdominal colour. It can be separated from 
<taxonomicName box="[620,733,940,966]" class="Insecta" family="Nemopteridae" genus="Nemopterella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="munroi">
<emphasis box="[620,733,940,966]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">A. munroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by being more yellowish in colour (
<figureCitation box="[1148,1236,939,966]" captionStart="FIGURES 96–101" captionStartId="49.[151,264,1916,1941]" captionTargetBox="[227,1358,587,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@49.[227,1361,587,1859]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURES 96–101. Afroptera spp. Thorax. 96, A. segregata (Tjeder); 97, A. remifera (Tjeder) 98, A. pilosa (Tjeder); 99, A. peringueyi (Tjeder); 100, A. parva (Tjeder); 101, A. exigua (Tjeder)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335152/files/figure.png" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Figs 96</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1249,1294,940,966]" captionStart="FIGURES 123–124" captionStartId="57.[151,264,1779,1804]" captionTargetBox="[227,1361,573,1737]" captionTargetId="figure@57.[227,1361,573,1737]" captionTargetPageId="57" captionText="FIGURES 123–124. Afroptera spp. 123, A. segregata (Tjeder), male holotype and associated labels; 124, A. remifera (Westwood), habitus ♀ and associated labels. Photos: Simon van Noort (SAMC)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335162/files/figure.png" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">123</figureCitation>
), with much longer body pubescence.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="69.[151,1437,796,1974]" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis box="[199,244,1012,1038]" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Size</emphasis>
(mm). Male: body length 10 (8.2–11.1); forewing 23.5 (20.9–26.3); hind wing 56.0 (47.5–63.4); antenna 22.4 (18.5–27.4). Female: body length 10 (7–11.5); forewing 21.8 (18.4–24.4); hind wing 47.0 (39–52.4); antenna 13.8 (12.6–15.9). (N = 31).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
